                            11.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Times New Roman","serif"'> </span><span
                            style='font-family:"Times New Roman","serif";mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Each
                            Ultra-short LASER pulses deposit small amount of energy in the sample. In the
                            case of High Repetition Rate (HRR) Laser, this individual heat accumulates in
                            the sample to the longer time scale. How this heating effect can be utilized to
                            study the chemical system.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
