                <section id="experiment-article-section-3">
                    <div class="icon" id="experiment-article-section-3-icon">
                    <img src="../images/procedure.jpg"></div>
                    <div class="heading" id="experiment-article-section-3-heading">
                        Procedure
                    </div>
                    <div class="content" id="experiment-article-section-3-content">
                        <div class="divContent">                           
                            <ol style='margin-top:0in' start=1 type=1>
                             <li class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:
                                 justify;line-height:normal;mso-list:l3 level1 lfo7'><span
                                 style='font-family:"Times New Roman","serif";mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Turn
                                 the IMRA LASER to standby for 10-15 minutes.<b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
                                 normal'><u><o:p></o:p></u></b></span></li>
                             <li class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;mso-list:l3 level1 lfo7'><span
                                 style='font-family:"Times New Roman","serif";mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Turn
                                 on the emission of 780nm (probe beam) and 1560nm (pump beam)<b
                                 style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><u><o:p></o:p></u></b></span></li>
                             <li class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;mso-list:l3 level1 lfo7'><span
                                 style='font-family:"Times New Roman","serif";mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Make
                                 the Mach-<span class=SpellE>Zehnder</span> Interferometer set-up using
                                 780nm and 1560 nm LASER beam.<b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><u><o:p></o:p></u></b></span></li>
                             <li class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;mso-list:l3 level1 lfo7'><span
                                 style='font-family:"Times New Roman","serif";mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Focus
                                 the final overlap beams of 780nm and 1560nm. <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
                                 normal'><u><o:p></o:p></u></b></span></li>
                             <li class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;mso-list:l3 level1 lfo7'><span
                                 style='font-family:"Times New Roman","serif";mso-ansi-language:EN-US'><span
                                 style='mso-spacerun:yes'>�</span>Now place another lens in the 780nm beam
                                 path, such that, the final 780 nm beam becomes collimated.<b
                                 style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><u><o:p></o:p></u></b></span></li>
                             <li class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;mso-list:l3 level1 lfo7'><span
                                 style='font-family:"Times New Roman","serif";mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Take
                                 the 40% of central portion of 780 nm by putting iris.<b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
                                 normal'><o:p></o:p></b></span></li>
                             <li class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;mso-list:l3 level1 lfo7'><span
                                 style='font-family:"Times New Roman","serif";mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Put
                                 the sample in experimental set-up and measured the transmittance through
                                 the aperture by changing the position of sample with respect the focal
                                 point of the focused laser. <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><o:p></o:p></b></span></li>
                             <li class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:
                                 justify;mso-list:l3 level1 lfo7'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman","serif";
                                 mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Plot the measured transmittance with respect to
                                 the position and calculate the Thermal Lens signal by following equation<b
                                 style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><o:p></o:p></b></span></li>
                            </ol>

                            <p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:
                            justify'><![if !msEquation]><span
                            lang=EN-IN style='font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";
                            mso-fareast-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman";
                            mso-ansi-language:EN-IN;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA'><![if !vml]><img width=149 height=46
                            src="Thermal files/image006.png" v:shapes="_x0000_i1025"><![endif]></span><![endif]><b
                            style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman","serif";
                            mso-ansi-language:EN-US'><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

                            <p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:
                            justify'><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman","serif";
                            mso-ansi-language:EN-US'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></b></p>

                            <p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman","serif";
                            mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>where <span class=SpellE><i>T<sub>p</sub></i></span>(<span
                            class=SpellE><i>&#955;</i><sub>e</sub></span>) and <i>T</i><sub>p0</sub> are
                            the probe transmittance through aperture in the presence and in the absence of
                            pump-beam, respectively<o:p></o:p></span></p>
    				    </div>
                    </div>
